The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Wednesday, December 31, 2003  Calcutta Column
 
	The spot behind St Xaviers College is in an unhygienic  condition, as local residents relieve themselves on the  street. The Corporation has already implemented a fine,  but the problem persists. Sterner action needs to be taken.  
	Md Tarique Nisar, Collin Street.  
	Ezra Street, between India Exchange Place and Canning Street,  which has no pavement, is usually blocked by goods vehicles  belonging to local traders. Pedestrians and vehicles have  a tough task making their way through the narrow passage.  Porters carrying luggage make it harder. The road needs  to be cleared.  
	Diptimoy Ghosh, Salt Lake.  
	As a large number of high-denomination currency notes are  in circulation, the UTI should stop issuing details when  subscribers draw money from ATMs, to avoid legal hazards. 
	 Govinda Bakshi, Budge Budge. 
